      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How long does the K-1 visa take in 2026?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The petition stage at USCIS currently takes 7–12 months. Add NVC forwarding (~4 weeks) and consular processing (~2 months) and the total to K-1 visa in hand is typically 9–15 months. The full timeline to a green card — including adjustment of status after marriage — is 21–40 months total."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I file Form I-129F online?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "No — as of 2026, Form I-129F must be filed by paper mail to the appropriate USCIS lockbox. USCIS has not yet added I-129F to its online filing system."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What happens if we don't marry within 90 days?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The K-1 visa expires and the foreign fiancé(e) must leave the United States. Staying beyond the 90 days without marrying is an immigration violation and can lead to removal proceedings and future bars to re-entry."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are common K-1 visa denial reasons?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
